Jared Slosberg

Bio

Im a fourth year PhD Candidate in the Department of Genetic Medicine at Johns Hopkins. I use (mostly) transcriptomic data to study age- and disease- associated changes in the enteric nervous system. Im passionate about open science and promoting reproducible computational research.

Check out my contributions to our recent preprint, where we identified and characterized a mesoderm-derived population of ganglionic cells that contribute to the enteric nervous system!

Education

2019 B.S. in Biomedical Engineering, George Washington University

2019-current PhD Candidate in Human Genetics- Advisor: Loyal Goff
